NOTES:
Classic blues lick with string bending.

Technique breakdown:
- 8b10 = Bend fret 8 up a whole step to pitch of fret 10
- r8 = Release bend back to fret 8
- 5h8 = Hammer from 5 to 8
- p5 = Pull off from 8 to 5
- ~ = Add vibrato (shake the string)
- 7b9 = Bend fret 7 up to pitch of fret 9

Tips:
- Bend with ring finger, support with middle and index
- Use ear to match bend pitch to target note
- Add aggressive vibrato on sustained notes
- Practice bending in tune!

LEGEND:
b = bend up (7b9 = bend 7 to sound like 9)
r = release bend
h = hammer-on
p = pull-off
~ = vibrato
